item.title: Ireland set for historic coalition govt
item.description: Ireland's new premier is set to be elected later after political rivals agreed to form an historic governing coalition.

item.title: Victoria records 41 new coronavirus cases
item.description: Victoria has 41 fresh coronavirus cases as it notches an 11th day of double-digit rises.

item.title: Drug-toting WA prison visitors face jail
item.description: Fines for prison visitors who try to bring in contraband have been increased six-fold in Western Australia and smugglers could also wind up behind bars themselves.

item.title: Victorian COVID-19 outbreak accelerates
item.description: Federal Treasurer Josh Frydenberg has warned of challenging and tough days ahead as his home state of Victoria reported another 41 fresh coronavirus infections, as the outbreak that started nearly a fortnight ago intensifies.

item.title: Search for boat crew member off Qld coast
item.description: A man has fallen off a sailing vessel in waters off central Queensland.

item.title: Second wave concern in Qld border decision
item.description: The Queensland government is considering opening up the state faster, but community transmission of the coronavirus in Victoria is a concern, says Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk.

item.title: Refusing virus test extends NSW quarantine
item.description: Returned international travellers who refuse to be tested for COVID-19 on the tenth day of hotel quarantine in NSW will be made to extend their stay by an extra 10 days.

item.title: ‘Game on’ to get more SA people moving
item.description: A new strategy encouraging more South Australians to increase their physical activity has the potential to save the public health system up to $804 million a year.

item.title: US COVID-19 infections near 2.5 million
item.description: The number of coronavirus cases has by 45,330 in the United States, its largest single-day spike since the pandemic began, taking the number of confirmed infections in the worst-hit country to 2.46 million.

item.title: Four killed in attack on Mexico top cop
item.description: Mexico City's chief of police was shot and injured and two of his bodyguards killed in a dramatic assassination attempt that he quickly blamed on one of Mexico's most powerful drug gangs, the Jalisco New Generation Cartel (CJNG).
